This paper is primarily focused on the optimization of wireless communication networks, which falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The use of deep reinforcement learning for optimization suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of information theory to maximize the signal to interference plus noise ratio (SINR), which suggests that it may also fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves the coordination of multiple agents (base stations) to optimize network performance, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
